<br>
The failure hasnt changed for you. You will still get the "A creature has detected you" message, and will know to back off. <br>
<br>
I have had no problems with this. Even on very "red" planets like dathomir. Using a combination of watching the radar screen and watching for broken scent messages, you can still effectively approach a nest. If you get  within 60 meters and no message, get closer .. if you get within 30 and no message, get closer. If you get right up next to it and mask scent breaks, turn around and high-tail it out and try again. Use burst when needed. <br>
<br>
Just cause you arent getting the "success" messages (e.g. you gain 128 scouting exp!), doesnt mean you cant use the failures. Besides -- its the failures you want to worry bout anyway ... thats what kills ya :)<br>
